    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Geolocation Utility Module\n\nThe implementation follows the exact same 3-layer pattern as `next/server` → `userAgent`:\n\n### Files to Create (5 total)\n\n1. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core source\n   - `Geo` interface (7 optional string fields)\n   - `COUNTRY_NAMES` map for 10 common country codes (AU, BR, CA, CN, DE, FR, GB, IN, JP, US)\n   - `geoFromHeaders(headers)` — reads all CDN headers; prefers `x-vercel-ip-country` over `cf-ipcountry` fallback\n   - `geo({ headers })` — thin wrapper matching the `userAgent` call signature\n   - `isInRegion(geo, regions)` — case-insensitive countryCode membership check\n   - `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)` — Haversine formula in km\n\n2. **`packages/next/geo.js`** — Public CommonJS entry (mirrors `server.js` pattern exactly)\n\n3. **`packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — Public type definitions (mirrors `server.d.ts` pattern; uses `export type` for the `Geo` interface)\n\n4. **`packages/next/package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` into the `files` array after `form.js`/`form.d.ts` (alphabetically, `g` follows `f`)\n\n5. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — Jest tests (matching the project's existing test framework) covering all functions, the Cloudflare fallback, missing headers, unknown country codes, and the NY→London distance (~5570 km ± 50 km)",
